column5: We are looking into Holinshead lake and possibly going to an outpost camp. Also parks fly-in service looks intresting. If you have been there or have any other suggesions we would be happy to hear from you. Thanks Mike

John-Sorry this took so long to reply but I have been going to Holinshead for the past 13 years and it is the greatest camp I've been to. Please e-mail me at [email protected] and I will be more than happy to help you out in any way. I have been to all the outposts and also the main base camp.

Been going to hollinshead for the past 8 years.Cabins are excellent, we never go to their outpost camps as the walleye and northern fishing is spectacular on Hollinshead. You will not regret going there. George{the owner} is a gracious host.

have heard nothing but good about holinshead.also have fished many outposts out of armstrong and they are fantastic.have a trip booked for june and need some guys to fill it up.if of interest contact [email protected]
